<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="116" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1866,2037]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,534,1902,1929]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Report associated with sponges:</emphasis>
This species was reported among 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hevers 1980)" baseAuthorityName="Hevers" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[923,1236,1903,1929]" class="Demospongiae" family="Spongillidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spongillida" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">
Spongillidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Hevers, J." box="[1079,1228,1903,1929]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" pagination="249 - 266" refId="ref16752" refString="Hevers, J. (1980) Morphologie und Systematik der Larven der Unionicola - Arten (Hydrachnellae, Acari) Deutschlands. Acarologia, 21 (2), 249 - 266." type="journal article" year="1980">Hevers 1980</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; nymph materials were obtained association with sponges (
<bibRefCitation author="Hevers, J." box="[659,808,1939,1965]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" pagination="73 - 92" refId="ref16721" refString="Hevers, J. (1979) Morphologie und Systematik der Nymphen der Unionicola-Arten (Hydrachnellae, Acari) Deutschlands. Osnabrucker Naturwissenschaftliche Mitteilungen, 6, 73 - 92." type="journal article" year="1979">Hevers 1979</bibRefCitation>
). A description of the annual cycles of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1776" box="[1249,1388,1939,1964]" class="Arachnida" family="Unionicolidae" genus="Unionicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis box="[1249,1388,1939,1964]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">U. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Soar" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[198,300,1975,2000]" class="Arachnida" family="Unionicolidae" genus="Unionicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[198,300,1975,2000]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">U. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was given by collecting samples in the field and by breeding different stages from sponge materials of 
<collectingCountry box="[228,363,2011,2037]" name="Netherlands" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Netherlands</collectingCountry>
(Davids 
<emphasis box="[466,515,2011,2037]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">et al</emphasis>
. 1979).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,150,285]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,151,177]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Soar" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[276,475,151,177]" class="Arachnida" family="Unionicolidae" genus="Unionicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[276,475,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">Unionicola minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Soar, C. D." box="[680,812,151,177]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" pagination="363 - 365" refId="ref19758" refString="Soar, C. D. (1900) British freshwater mites. Science-Gossip, London, New Series, 6 (72), 363 - 365." type="journal article" year="1900">Soar (1900)</bibRefCitation>
as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1776" box="[1024,1161,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Unionicolidae" genus="Unionicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis box="[1024,1161,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">U. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(M 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1202,1218,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">Ã¼</emphasis>
ller). 
<bibRefCitation author="Hevers, J." box="[1278,1431,150,177]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" refId="ref16652" refString="Hevers, J. (1975) Zur Systematik und Biologie der einheimeschen Unionicola-Arten (Hydrachnellae: Acari). Doctoral Dissertation, University of Kiel, Kiel, 354 pp." type="book" year="1975">Hevers (1975</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hevers, J." box="[198,257,187,213]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" pagination="691 - 703" refId="ref16684" refString="Hevers, J. (1977) Revision der in Deutschland Vorkommenden Arten der Untergattung Unionicola s. str. (Hydrachnellae, Acari). Acarologia, 18 (4), 691 - 703." type="journal article" year="1977">1977</bibRefCitation>
, 1978) thoroughly reviewed its systematic position and established 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Soar" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[1013,1114,187,212]" class="Arachnida" family="Unionicolidae" genus="Unionicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[1013,1114,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">U. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a species distinct from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1776" class="Arachnida" family="Unionicolidae" genus="Unionicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">U. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Molecular analysis of these water mites was done and confirmed 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Soar" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[1043,1144,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Unionicolidae" genus="Unionicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[1043,1063,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1077,1144,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid species (
<bibRefCitation author="Stalstedt, J. &amp; Bergsten, J. &amp; Ronquist, F." pageId="15" pageNumber="116" pagination="3415 - 3435" refId="ref19822" refString="Stalstedt, J., Bergsten, J. &amp; Ronquist, F. (2013) &quot; Forms &quot; of water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia): intraspecific variation or valid species? Ecology and Evolution, 3 (10), 3415 - 3435. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / ece 3.704" type="journal article" year="2013">
Stalstedt 
<emphasis box="[198,247,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
